title: Denver Recording Artists PME Music Release New Music Video, "I Can't Breathe"
text:
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes announces the release of the new music video by PME Music currently seeking blog placements and interviews.
Denver, CO (PRWEB) October 05, 2015
Today Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes announces the release of “I Can't Breathe”, the latest music video by PME Music. The video can be viewed in its entirety at the Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes website .
PME Music is currently seeking press opportunities, interviews, features, and more. They can be reached through their official website .
About PME MUSIC: PME MUSIC is a team of individual artist, which consist of GI FLOW, KING, and C DA BEAST.
Lonnie Allen Wright III " GI FLOW " was born September 10, 1992; To Lonnie Wright, Son of former Denver Broncos & Denver Rocket's player Lonnie Wright. Hope Shazier, his mother, is Roger Troutman's 3rd born child, making stardom imminent for this young, rebellious, but charismatic MC currently living in his birth place of Denver, Colorado.
King Burtt aka KING was born March 27, 1994 to his dad, Jessie Burtt aka Dolla Ill and his mother Dawn O’Neill. Born and raised in Aurora, CO, King was gifted from a young age with talent, but through dedication and hard work he has been able to shine as an athlete and as an artist.
Charles D. Robinson Jr. aka "C DA BEAST" Is a Sourthen rapper straight out of Lake Charles Louisiana. Born 1984 to Tina and Charles on Dec 22. 3 days before Christmas Tina considered it an early gift. By the age of 9, He was already performing at local venues in the city doing what he does best.
For more info on PME Music visit their official Facebook fan page .
About Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes:
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes are the most widely distributed mixtapes in the world, with over 100 million downloads/plays generated by over 300 volumes officially hosted by major artists. Coast 2 Coast has a solid reach in the new music industry with a digital magazine, DJ coalition, industry tips blog, yearly convention, and more. Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes represents a unique opportunity for artists of all urban genres, from major to indie. For more information, visit http://www.coast2coastmixtapes.com .
